org.sbml.squeezer
Class ReactionType

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.squeezer.ReactionType

public class ReactionType
extends java.lang.Object

The purpose of this class is to analyze a reaction object for several properties, such as the number of reactants and products, the types of modifiers and their number, if the stoichiometries are always integer numbers or real valued and much more. With this information at hand the reaction type is able to suggest applicable kinetic equations from the list of available kinetic laws and also to select the default kinetic equation for this specific type. This class can also answer several questions regarding a reaction, for instance, whether a reaction is follows a bi-bi mechanism. This can be used for GUIs to display reaction properties to a user.

Since:
1.3
Author:
Andreas Dräger andreas.draeger@uni-tuebingen.de
